@lillolollo this issue was never present for me in 2.10.12, but as of upgrading to 2.10.14 this morning, I am now having this issue. Intended steps:

1. Alpha to Selection of intended layer;
2. Filters > Decor > Add Bevel;
3. Set thickness at "5"; Uncheck "work on copy", leave "keep bump layer" unchecked; click "OK";
4. The filter appears to run through its steps, but upon completion, no change to the layer appears to have been made.

I am having this issue across two separate machines:
1. Work PC: Windows 10 Pro 1903
2. Home PC: Windows 10 Home 1909

Attached are two screenshots. The first was created in October 2019 on GIMP 2.10.12, note the visible bevel;
The second was created this morning after applying the bevel filter. No visible results.

![Bevel-add-2_10_12](/uploads/8406d4442f1d66357f667f426b99e90f/Bevel-add-2_10_12.png)

![Bevel-add-2_10_14](/uploads/93d417b164b9a6640739f0ae82a3f366/Bevel-add-2_10_14.png)

